      <title outputclass="H3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">8.004</ph> Use of other sources.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p otherprops="Body"
            outputclass="Body"
            class="- topic/p "
            id="d450e13">If an agency is unable to satisfy requirements for supplies and services from the mandatory sources listed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i8_002.dita#i8_002"
                     base="i1118176"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">8.002</xref>
            </ph> and <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i8_003.dita#i8_003"
                     base="i1118206"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">8.003</xref>
            </ph>, agencies are encouraged to consider satisfying requirements from or through the non-mandatory sources listed in paragraph (a) of this section (not listed in any order of priority) before considering the non-mandatory source listed in paragraph (b) of this section. When satisfying requirements from non-mandatory sources, see <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1118935.dita#i1118935"
                     base="i1118935"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">7.105</xref>
            </ph>(b) and <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1101928.dita#i1101928"
                     base="i1101928"
                     outputclass="fm:Part"
                     class="- topic/xref ">part  19</xref>
            </ph> regarding consideration of small business, veteran-owned small business, service-disabled veteran-owned small business, HUBZone small business, small disadvantaged business (including 8(a) participants), and women-owned small business concerns.</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d443e40">
            <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="H5_6abc123"
                outputclass="H5_6abc123"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d450e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d443e50">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d450e54" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        Supplies. Federal Supply Schedules, Governmentwide acquisition contracts, multi-agency contracts, and any other procurement instruments intended for use by multiple agencies, including blanket purchase agreements (BPAs) under Federal Supply Schedule contracts (e.g., Federal Strategic Sourcing Initiative (FSSI) agreements accessible at <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">http://www.gsa.gov/fssi</xref>(see also <xref href="FAR-i1120374.dita#i1120374"
                              base="i1120374"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">5.601</xref>)).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d450e69" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        Services. Agencies are encouraged to consider Federal Prison Industries, Inc., as well as the sources listed in paragraph (a)(1) of this section (see <xref href="FAR-i1117091.dita#i1117091"
                              base="i1117091"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d450e83" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  Commercial sources (including educational and non-profit institutions) in the open market.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
